dcterms:description: Synthetic dataset in the form of a regular grid 100 × 100. Each cell in the grid is a node, and the edges for each cell are at most 8. The cells can be labeled as mines or traversable ones.
dcterms:title: Minesweeper

dcterms:description: Graph based on data from a question-answering website. Nodes represent users, while edges connect them if they have interacted during a certain interval. The users are classified as active or non-active depending on whether they remained so during that interval of time.
dcterms:title: Questions
